==French==
===Etymology===
Mediaeval Latin [[baccalaureatus]], from [[baccalaureus]], an alteration of [[baccalarius]] ‘young man aspiring to knighthood’ to resemble [[bacca lauri]] ‘laurel berry’ (the ancient symbol of victory).

